PRODUCTION OUTLOOK

THE COMPANY ESTIMATES ITS AVERAGE WORLDWIDE OIL-EQUIVALENT PRODUCTION IN

2015

WILL BE FLAT TO 3 PERCENT GROWTH COMPARED TO 2014. THIS ESTIMATE IS SUBJECT TO MANY FACTORS AND UNCERTAINTIES, AS DESCRIBED BEGINNING ON PAGE FS-4. REFER TO THE “REVIEW OF ONGOING EXPLORATION AND PRODUCTION ACTIVITIES IN KEY AREAS,” BEGINNING ON PAGE 8, FOR A DISCUSSION OF THE COMPANY’S MAJOR CRUDE OIL AND NATURAL GAS DEVELOPMENT PROJECTS.

