, THE COMPANY HAD PURCHASED

180.9

MILLION SHARES FOR

$20.0

BILLION. GIVEN THE CHANGE IN MARKET CONDITIONS, THE COMPANY IS SUSPENDING THE SHARE REPURCHASE PROGRAM FOR 2015.

