. THE FEDERAL SUPERFUND LAW AND ANALOGOUS STATE LAWS PROVIDE FOR JOINT AND SEVERAL LIABILITY FOR ALL RESPONSIBLE PARTIES. ANY FUTURE ACTIONS BY THE EPA OR OTHER REGULATORY AGENCIES TO REQUIRE CHEVRON TO ASSUME OTHER POTENTIALLY RESPONSIBLE PARTIES’ COSTS AT DESIGNATED HAZARDOUS WASTE SITES ARE NOT EXPECTED TO HAVE A MATERIAL EFFECT ON THE COMPANY’S RESULTS OF OPERATIONS, CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL POSITION OR LIQUIDITY.

